('ONET-MATERIALS_ENGINEERS', 'source_onet_materials_engineers', 'Materials Engineers', 'Materials Engineers is an imported ONET role/occupation concept. It needs TALLENTIN normalization before production routing.', 'role_title', 'Evaluate materials and develop machinery and processes to manufacture materials for use in products that must meet specialized design and performance specifications. Develop new uses for known materials. Includes those engineers working with composite materials or specializing in one type of material, such as graphite, metal and metal alloys, ceramics and glass, plastics and polymers, and naturally occurring materials. Includes metallurgists and metallurgical engineers, ceramic engineers, and welding engineers.', ARRAY['Automotive Sheet Metal Engineer','Ceramic Design Engineer','Ceramic Engineer','Ceramic Research Engineer','Ceramics Test Engineer','Corrosion Engineer','Design Engineer','Engineer','Extractive Metallurgist','Extrusion Engineer','Failure Analysis Engineer','Forensic Materials Engineer','Foundry Metallurgist','Foundry Process Engineer','Glass Science Engineer','Green Building Materials Designer','Material Analyst','Material Science And Testing Engineer','Materials Development Engineer','Materials Engineer','Materials Research Engineer','Metallographer','Metallurgical Engineer','Metallurgical Specialist','Metallurgist','Physical Metallurgist','Plastics Engineer','Plating Engineer','Polymer Engineer','Process Metallurgist','Project Engineer','Research Engineer','Smelting Engineer','Stress Engineer','Supplier Quality Engineer (SQE)','Test Engineer','Testing Engineer','Welding Engineer']::text[], ARRAY['Materials Engineers','Automotive Sheet Metal Engineer','Ceramic Design Engineer','Ceramic Engineer','Ceramic Research Engineer','Ceramics Test Engineer','Corrosion Engineer','Design Engineer','Engineer','Extractive Metallurgist','Extrusion Engineer','Failure Analysis Engineer','Forensic Materials Engineer','Foundry Metallurgist','F